					<description><![CDATA[<p>Funding Boosts Growth and Operations CertifID, based in Austin, Texas, just raised $47.5 million in Series C funding, with Centana Growth Partners leading the round. The funding was led by</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/certifid-raises-47-5m/" data-wpel-link="internal">CertifID Raises $47.5M To Strengthen Real Estate Fraud Protection</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>Funding Boosts Growth and Operations</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">CertifID, based in Austin, Texas, just raised $47.5 million in Series C funding, with Centana Growth Partners leading the round. The funding was led by Centana Growth Partners. The capital will help CertifID expand its operations and accelerate development efforts. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">CEO Tyler Adams said the investment strengthens the company’s ability to protect billions of dollars in real estate transactions each month. CertifID safeguards transactions with advanced software, direct insurance coverage, and proven recovery services. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">CertifID protects the real estate world from wire fraud, backing every deal they handle with up to $5 million in coverage. Their clients? Title companies, law firms, lenders, real estate agents, even home buyers and sellers. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">They also have an office up in Grand Rapids, Michigan. With fresh funding, CertifID plans to expand its services and strengthen fraud protection. That matters more than ever, especially since scammers seem to get smarter every year.</span></p>
<h2><b>Leadership Expansion Strengthens Expertise</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">With this new funding, CertifID brought on two key leaders: Josh Linn as Chief Product Officer and Liz Conn as Chief Marketing Officer. Linn comes with more than 20 years in banking, payments, and fintech, holding senior product roles at major banks and, most recently, at Socure—which is known for </span><a href="https://www.trulioo.com/identity-verification-use-cases/digital-identity-verification" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">digital identity verification</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Linn holds two published patents and two pending patents in identity resolution and knowledge graph systems. He has advised organisations on AI governance frameworks in finance and government sectors.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">As CPO, Linn will oversee product, design, and data strategy. His focus will be on making real estate closings faster, smarter, and more secure. “Wire fraud in real estate isn’t a niche problem,” Linn said. “It’s one of the most consequential identity and payments challenges in financial services today. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">CertifID allows us to protect transactions at scale and create the foundation for broader financial platforms.” Conn brings extensive experience in B2B SaaS marketing. She previously served as SVP of Marketing at Sayari and led growth marketing at Logi Analytics, which was acquired by Insight Software. Conn will lead CertifID’s brand strategy and awareness campaigns.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">“Wire fraud is one of the most urgent crises in real estate,” Conn said. “Most consumers don’t know the risks until it’s too late. We have an opportunity to change that story and make transactions safer for everyone.”</span></p>
<h2><b>Protecting Billions from Fraud<br />
</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_199750" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-199750" class="size-full wp-image-199750" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/a-futuristic-neon-lit-poster-showcasing-_HzFg5j3KSBq0TL8Sw11HUg_Q-ZY6lydT7qQzi5LYsRQKw_cover.png" alt="CertifID prevents large-scale real estate fraud using secure verification systems and recovery-backed protection" width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-199750" class="wp-caption-text">CertifID continues to block millions in fraud, combining technology, insurance, and recovery services to secure real estate transactions. Source: Created by Ventureburn</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">CertifID has a strong track record in fraud prevention. In 2025 alone, the platform blocked over $285 million in confirmed fraudulent transactions. It also verified more than 1.5 million mortgage payoffs and returned over $126 million to fraud victims.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company combines automated software with direct insurance coverage and recovery support. This approach gives real estate pros and their clients real peace of mind. They can close deals knowing their money is safe.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Tyler Adams, the CEO, sees the threat clearly. &#8220;Attacks are getting smarter and more common—it&#8217;s kind of shocking. Bringing Josh and Liz on board is a big move for us. We&#8217;re working together to raise the bar for security in every important deal,&#8221; he said.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/pharos-raises-44m-to-expand-its-on-chain-economy/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Pharos Raises $44M to Expand Its On-Chain Economy</span></a></p>
<h2><b>Market Opportunity and Future Plans</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The funding will support CertifID’s expansion into new markets and the scaling of existing services. It will also accelerate the development of tools that streamline real estate transactions while enhancing security.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">CertifID’s vision extends beyond fraud protection. The platform aims to create an infrastructure of trust around identity and payments. This could form the foundation for broader financial services anchored to the real estate market.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">CertifID isn’t going solo. They’ve got solid investors behind them, plus a leadership team that really gets it. The company keeps pushing its platform forward, adding to the team, and locking down big transactions. That’s even more important now, with everything going digital and risks popping up faster than ever.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">To stay updated on crypto venture capital funding and market trends, visit our </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/category/news/venture-capital/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">venture capital news section</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> for more insights</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/certifid-raises-47-5m/" data-wpel-link="internal">CertifID Raises $47.5M To Strengthen Real Estate Fraud Protection</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
